
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class School {
    - name: String
    - principal: Teacher
}

class Teacher {
    - firstName: String
    - lastName: String
    - email: String
}

class Student {
    - firstName: String
    - lastName: String
}

class ClassGroup {
    - name: String
    - minStudents: int = 10
    - maxStudents: int = 31
}

class Room {
    - name: String
}

class Classroom extends Room {
    - capacity: int
}

class OtherRoom extends Room {
    - size: double // in square meters
}

' Associations and relationships

School "1" -- "1..*" Teacher : employs\nas teacher |
Teacher "1" -- "1" School : is principal of <<aggregation>> |
Teacher "1" -- "0..3" School : teaches at |
School "1" -- "1" Principal : has <<aggregation>> |

Student "1" -- "1" School : attends |
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : is member of |
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Classroom : uses classroom |
Classroom "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : is used by |

Teacher "1" -- "1" School : can be principal of (max 1) |
School "1" -- "1" Principal : has principal |

note right of Principal
    A Principal is a Teacher who
    acts as the head of a School.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **Inheritance**: `Classroom` and `OtherRoom` inherit from `Room`.
- **Multiplicity**:
  - A `Teacher` can teach at up to 3 schools (`0..3`).
  - A `Student` belongs to exactly one `ClassGroup`, which uses exactly one `Classroom`.
  - A `ClassGroup` has between 10 and 31 students.
- **Aggregation/Composition**:
  - `School` contains one `Principal` (a `Teacher`), represented with aggregation.
  - A `ClassGroup` is assigned to exactly one `Classroom`.

